name: Emily B
text: The signs posted say they open 1 hour - 30 minutes before a train arrives. Usually the station opens 3-5 minutes before a train, so I cannot even get dropped off by transport. You can't wait outside either, its a very bad part of town to be alone and outside. I really dislike how impromptu they are open opening only minutes before a train, but its better than the hassle of the Birmingham station. Please be more reliable in the future.

name: Dee Smith
text: This is my first visit to this station. Can't speak a lot about the service. But I can say when I was getting off the train the staff, from the birmingham station did offer to help me down from the train . The porters for the baggage were not very accommodating I had to flag them down and then they still didn't give me any assistance.. the station appears to be clean and well kept. It's very small from what I can see as I said I wasn't there long enough to really notice much.

name: TrainMan
text: My son trainboy14 he’s 14 years old and he loves taking picture of trains

name: Liss Sterling
text:
No parking area due to ongoing construction of new terminal. If there is one, there is no signage to direct you. The old station looks like an abandoned derelict. Minimal staff. When I picked up my daughter yesterday, no one was manning the window inside, so I just had to guess where to go.

Hopefully, all this will improve once the new terminal is finished, but it appears to be way behind schedule.

This station is a black mark on the city. I bet thru passengers look at this and are very glad they aren't getting off the train in Birmingham.

And the train was running 1:45 late yesterday. And her train to NOLA was super late 3 weeks ago. Looks like a pattern.

name: Scott King
text: This is a clean and comfortable station. The staff on hand are friendly and helpful. There is on site security for those who would want to know. There are many vending machines here and there is a small cafe available just across the street.  This facility is well designed for comfort and is bright and airy.  There are abundant outlets for charging your electronics throughout and free WiFi as well.

name: Timothy Richey
text: Awesome staff who handled a unpleasant situation that was out of their control very well

name: Stephanie Z Evans
text: PJ at the ticket and baggage counter is incredibly and intentionally rude. Helping customers with baggage check and ticketing is the expectation as he is behind that counter but he goes out of his way to be rude and condescending. There is absolutely zero focus on customer service or experience.

name: Meeka Acklin
text: The train station was clean. 2.5 hour delay. Scheduled to get to New Orleans at 7:32. Got pushed back to 11. First time rider & asked questions to very rude staff. Too many delays. Too many slow downs. But the ride back was much smoother & more pleasant

name: L Jarod Pearson (TARP)
text: The new Amtrak station in Birmingham is nothing at all like the old one!  The old station was in a dark tunnel.  The new station is bright and open with security on site and a view of the city on all sides.  You can make easy bus connections now because new station has Greyhound, Maxx transit, and Megabus all on the same property.  There's a cafe on site and several restaurants within a short walk.  Railroad park is about two blocks away.  This is one of the best train stations in the South!  Atlanta needs one just like it!

name: C J
text: Fun day trip.  Friendly riders and station staff.

name: Bri Chivatero
text: This is a really nice transportation station. They have lots of chairs, some tables, and everyone is very nice. (All of my information is based on Amtrak, although they definitely have Greyhound too.) If you have trouble lifting things up stairs, whether from strength or height, either check your bags or ask them to help you. You have to go up stairs to get to the trains, and if it weren't for a very nice boy, I would not have managed to get up there with my suitcase and box. They were very easy to communicate with; while they couldn't do anything to get my train to actually show up on time, they made sure we knew when it was there and how to get to the train once it arrived.

name: Juli Young
text: Station itself is pretty bad. Bathrooms are atrocious. One stall has no door, others have no locks. Dimly lit. Floors throughout station are very worn. Waiting area has old worn seats and benches. There are no vending machines. No real parking, only curbside or park and walk. No wifi, and you can barely get a signal. At least it's halfway warm inside.

name: Wilson Ricketts
text: Strong amount of dinge but can't say it lacks character. The lobby feels like it was designed for a David Lynch movie and populated with colorful characters. Looking forward to seeing what the new station will be like when construction is completed.

name: Gregory Bazile
text: The new terminal looks great. It looks nice and clean. This is a significant improvement over what Birmingham had before. Great job.

name: Paul Spadoni
text: Disregard anything you read about this station before. It is now brand new, shiny, clean. You can connect your phone and computer to recharge. You have free wifi. Friendly security guards are eager to help you find your way. There are new vending machines. It's a first class facility.

name: SouthernSignalProductions
text: When I went all the staff was friendly. When we left to go eat they kept our bags behind the counter. Amtrak employees were very nice. Hope to go back.

text: Head and shoulders better than the former station on Morris Avenue . As part of the Birmingham Intermodal Facility that opened in early 2018, the Amtrak Birmingham Station is joined with a new parking structure, the Greyhound Station, and the Birmingham Metro Area eXpress station. The new facility also includes a new cafe.
